body: "## Context\nWindows-specific handling found in tests:\n- tests/unit/test-all-command.spec.ts line 896: extended timeout on win32\n- tests/unit/test-command.spec.ts line 1820: signal fixture skip on win32\n- tests/unit/vector-store-adapter.spec.ts line 663: itOnPosix skip on win32\n\nBut: fs-utils.spec.ts and store-paths.spec.ts have no win32-conditional tests.\n\nNightly actually runs full test suite on windows-latest (not just smoke), so any path-separator bugs would surface there, but are not proactively tested in unit coverage.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- fs-utils.spec.ts has at least one test verifying path construction on simulated win32 (or a comment explaining the platform is safe)\n- store-paths.spec.ts verifies path outputs are platform-appropriate\n- OR: a review of fs-utils.ts and paths.ts confirms path.join() is used throughout with no hardcoded separators\n\n## Evidence\ntests/unit/fs-utils.spec.ts; tests/unit/store-paths.spec.ts; tests/unit/test-all-command.spec.ts line 896; nightly.yml windows-latest entry"
